<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-650-819  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 650 819.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Dec 4 1990 v4 n41 p6(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Mac Portable replacement on track for S.F. expo delivery.andO;(upgraded portable microcomputer ready for 1991 Macworld Expo inSan Francisco)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Cohen, Raines.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Apple Computer Inc. (Product enhancement).andO;Ticker:    AAPL.andO;Product:   Apple Macintosh Portable (Portable computer) (Productenhancement).andO;Topic:     UpgradingEnhancementsPortable ComputersMacWorld ExpositionPricing PolicyDisplays.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Mac Portable replacement on track for S.F.andP;  expo deliveryandM;Cupertino, Calif.andP;  -- A new version of the Macintosh Portable, addressingsome of the problems that have kept sales of the machine far below Apple'sexpectations, is on track for introduction next month at Macworld Expo in SanFrancisco.andM;As reported previously (see MacWEEK, Oct. 23), the upgraded Portable willhave an improved, backlit screen and a lower price and weight, but it willnot represent a major departure from Apple's sole entry in the burgeoningportable market to date.andM;In the second major price cut since the machine's introduction in September1989 (see MacWEEK, April 20), Apple is expected to cut about $500 to $1,500from the cost of the Macintosh Portable, depending on configuration.andM;Although the new backlit display reportedly adds significantly to the cost ofthe machine, sources said Apple has achieved enough savings on othermanufacturing costs to make up the difference.andP;  For instance, by substitutingpseudostatic RAM for the true static RAM currently used, Apple is trading offbattery life for cost savings.andM;This is the end of the line for the original Mac Portable model.andP;  Sourcessaid that the company may offer a dealer- or factory-based upgrade forPortable owners.andP;  The upgrade could cost at least $800, sources said.andM;Sources said Apple will distribute a list of third-party Portable add-ons, inHyperCard stack and paper form, at Macworld Expo next month.andP;  In addition,attendees will see the new Portable at a number of developer booths.andO;</TEXT></DOC>